result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Omar Shariffie Parker

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Omar Shariffie Parker not in court, in custody.  Attorney Amanda Poznanski not in court.  
Attorney Stephan Eduard Nolten in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for a Status Conference. Defendant has been extradited. State moves for Dismissal of this action.
Upon motion of State, Court ordered case DISMISSED.

Defendant Omar Shariffie Parker in court with attorney Ashley Fard.  Defendant Omar Shariffie Parker in custody.  Gregg Herman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Omar Shariffie Parker appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Kies, Branch 45.  Pursuant to Chief Judge Directive 22-04, parties are hereby notified that as of July 30, 2022, this case will be assigned to Branch 19, Judge Kori Ashley, in Room 313 of the Safety Building.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of MINNESOTA.  Defendant contested extradition.  Court ordered Defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Status conference scheduled for August 29, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
